Referencing #5250 since it seems to apply...

From the shell if I sha256sum a file I get a large 64-hexdigit (256-bit) sha256 hash, but if I use File.get_sha256() on the same file it is a totally different hash that is only 32-hexdigits (128-bit) long (sha256 hashes should all be same length: 256-bit or 64 hexdigits printed), suggesting there is a bug (wrong sha256 algorithm???).
Further inspection indicates the result from File.get_sha256() matches using md5sum on the file from the terminal. So Godot is not making an sha256, it's making an md5. That needs to be either renamed or made to use the proper algorithm.

PS: There is a File.get_md5() already so they should not both do the same thing with one advertising something else.

```
func _ready():
    var f=File.new()
    var sha=f.get_sha256("res://engine.cfg")
    var md5=f.get_md5("res://engine.cfg")
    print(sha)
    print(md5)
```
